cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the alignment of sequential data, specifically video to text, which falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper proposes an end-to-end neural architecture that uses Long Short-term Memory (LSTM) blocks, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG and cs.AI also likely sub-categories. Finally, the experiments involve real datasets, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
